    "body": "When creating new package recipes, I often have to use `spack clean` to remove left-over previous partial builds. This also deletes the downloaded archives, and re-downloading them takes time. As the downloaded files have checksums, this shouldn't be necessary, and a general download cache (outside of the staging directories etc.) would make sense.\n",
